<b>Meredith Edwards</b> (<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../805/15805.xml">
10 June</link> <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../595/34595.xml">
1917</link> - <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../360/11360.xml">
8 February</link> <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../553/34553.xml">
1999</link>) was a Welsh <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../282/383282.xml">
character actor</link> and writer.</p>
<p>

Edwards was born in <region wordnetid="108630985" confidence="0.8">
<village wordnetid="108672738" confidence="0.8">
<location wordnetid="100027167" confidence="0.8">
<settlement wordnetid="108672562" confidence="0.8">
<geographical_area wordnetid="108574314" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../929/1301929.xml">
Rhosllannerchrugog</link></geographical_area>
</settlement>
</location>
</village>
</region>
, <region wordnetid="108630985" confidence="0.8">
<area wordnetid="108497294" confidence="0.8">
<location wordnetid="100027167" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../126/359126.xml">
Denbighshire</link></location>
</area>
</region>
, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../894/69894.xml">
Wales</link>.  He is the father of actor <link>
Ioan Meredith</link>, and the grandfather of actors <link>
Ifan Meredith</link> and <link>
Rhys Meredith</link></p>
<p>

His film appearances include <it><movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../958/11705958.xml">
A Run for Your Money</link></movie>
</it> (1949), <it><movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../305/421305.xml">
The Blue Lamp</link></movie>
</it> (1950), <it><movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../632/156632.xml">
The Lavender Hill Mob</link></movie>
</it> (1951), <it><movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../912/1401912.xml">
The Cruel Sea</link></movie>
</it> (1953), <it><movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../552/1222552.xml">
Dunkirk</link></movie>
</it> (1958) and <it><movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../083/8772083.xml">
Tiger Bay</link></movie>
</it> (1959).</p>
<p>

He appeared as the murderous butler in the cult television series <it><link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../606/662606.xml">
Randall and Hopkirk (Deceased)</link></it> in 1969, and as Tom in the cult children's Science Fiction serial <it><link>
Sky</link></it> in 1975.</p>
<p>

He was a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../003/83003.xml">
conscientious objector</link> in the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../927/32927.xml">
Second World War</link>, serving in the <link>
Non-Combatant Corps</link> before being seconded to the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../699/9224699.xml">
National Fire Service</link> in Liverpool and London. He stood as <party wordnetid="108256968" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../343/53343.xml">
Plaid Cymru</link></party>
 candidate for <body wordnetid="107965085" confidence="0.8">
<social_group wordnetid="107950920" confidence="0.8">
<constituency wordnetid="108238156" confidence="0.8">
<group wordnetid="100031264" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../598/7442598.xml">
Denbigh</link></group>
</constituency>
</social_group>
</body>
 in the 1966 <election wordnetid="100181781" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
